# Additional allowed domains for firewall whitelist
#
# The init-firewall.sh script automatically reads domains from:
#   /workspace/.devcontainer/allowed-domains.txt
#
# To use this file:
#   1. Copy or rename this file to 'allowed-domains.txt'
#   2. Add your custom domains below (one per line)
#   3. Comments (lines starting with #) and empty lines are ignored
#
# The base container already allows these domains (hardcoded):
#   - registry.npmjs.org (npm packages)
#   - api.anthropic.com (OpenCode AI)
#   - sentry.io, statsig.anthropic.com, statsig.com (analytics)
#   - marketplace.visualstudio.com (VS Code extensions)
#   - vscode.blob.core.windows.net (VS Code updates)
#   - update.code.visualstudio.com (VS Code updates)
#
# Example custom domains:
# myapi.example.com
# cdn.example.com
# database.mycompany.com
# storage.googleapis.com
